# shadcn/ui (frontend)

Use [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) for **all** UI primitives in the Next.js app under `frontend/`. Never hand-roll raw `<input>`, `<button>`, `<select>`, `<dialog>`, etc. when a shadcn equivalent exists.

Config: [components.json](mdc:frontend/components.json) · Style: `base-nova` · Icons: `lucide-react`

---

## CLI (run from `frontend/`)

Initialize (only if `components.json` is missing):
```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

Add a missing component (replace `button` with any component name from the shadcn docs):
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Common components: `button`, `input`, `card`, `dialog`, `dropdown-menu`, `form`, `label`, `select`, `sheet`, `toast`, `tabs`, `badge`, `avatar`, `separator`, `skeleton`.

---

## File locations

| Type | Path |
|------|------|
| shadcn primitives (auto-generated, do not edit) | `@/components/ui/` |
| Custom composite components | `@/components/` |
| Shared utilities (`cn`) | `@/lib/utils` |

---

## `cn()` for class merging

Always merge Tailwind classes with `cn()` from [@/lib/utils](mdc:frontend/src/lib/utils.ts):
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
<div className={cn('base-class', conditional && 'extra-class', className)} />
```

## Custom variants with `cva`

Use `class-variance-authority` (already installed) for components with multiple variants:
```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

const badge = cva('rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium', {
  variants: {
    variant: { default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground', muted: 'bg-muted text-muted-foreground' },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'default' },
});
```

---

## Tailwind v4 — CSS-based theming

This project uses **Tailwind v4**. There is no `tailwind.config.ts`. All design tokens (colors, radius, fonts) are CSS variables defined in [@/app/globals.css](mdc:frontend/src/app/globals.css).

- Use semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.) instead of raw color values like `bg-gray-100`.
- Do **not** add a `tailwind.config.ts` to customize the theme; extend tokens in `globals.css` under `@theme inline` instead.

## Dark mode

Dark mode uses the `.dark` class strategy (toggle `dark` on `<html>`). Color tokens automatically switch via CSS variables — no extra `dark:` overrides needed for standard semantic tokens.

---

## Icons

Use `lucide-react` (already installed) for all icons:
```tsx
import { Search, ChevronDown } from 'lucide-react';
<Search className="h-4 w-4" />
```

Do not install a second icon library.

---

## RSC & `'use client'`

- `rsc: true` is set — shadcn components that use hooks or browser APIs are already marked `'use client'` inside `@/components/ui/`.
- Pages and layouts are Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when the component itself needs state, effects, or event handlers.
